asset.hookText: http://www.skis.com/Rome-Hammerhead-Snowboard-2013/271167,default,pd.html  Must people thought sharks are only found in the ocean, not anymore. Rome has introduced the first snow shark code named The Hammerhead. The Hammerhead eats up the park with tail slashing butters and incredible board slides all day long. Skatecore Profiling with a Pop Core allows the snowboard to be softer in between the bindings and a stiffer nose and tail makes the Hammerhead feel like a skateboard for turning and ollieing. ButterOut Transition Zones allow for a increase in control when throwing your butters around, guaranteed to fuel your addiction. The Quickrip Sidecut technology lets the board ride loose and playful at slow speeds, and powerful and precise at higher speeds. Impact base protect the Hammerhead from poachers and rails.
